topic.title: Human Clinical Subject Data Document Section - conformance rules

section.p: The document is divided into sections as defined by the user. It is reccomended that, with the exeception of the generic "add-on" templates: related records, supplemental values, comments, findings about, each section contain a single type of the possible listed templates, that is, the content of a single SDTM domain. In the case of the visit template, this allows for inclusion of data from other SDTM defined data structures (domain) to be included within the section. The user is also free to create custom sections based on the included generic templates: Study Subject Finding, Study Subject Event, Study Subject Intervention.

ol.li: SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] @classCode="DOCSECT" (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.6 HL7ActClass) (CONF:175)
SHALL contain zero or one [0..1] @moodCode="EVN" Event (CodeSystem: 2.16.840.1.113883.5.1001 HL7ActMood) (CONF:176)

A code to indicate the nature of the section. This code should indicate the primary domain association for the section.

MAY contain zero or one [0..1] entry (CONF:179)
The section may include a record based on the defined template. It should also include a record based on the study arm template.
Contains exactly one [1..1] Human Clinical Subject Demographics (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.46)

SHOULD contain zero or more [0..*] entry (CONF:180)
The section may include one or many records based on the defined template.
Contains exactly one [1..1] Subject Element (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.93)

SHOULD contain zero or more [0..*] entry (CONF:181)
If a visit entry is included, the section will only contain visit entries. Note, however, that several other SDTM domains will have their data nested within this entry as shown by the Visit template.
Contains exactly one [1..1] Visit (templateId: 2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.23.100)

If included, the section will only contain Concommitant Medication entries.

Such concommitantMedicationAssociations SHALL contain exactly one [1..1] substanceAdministration, where its type is Concomitant Medication (CONF:200)
